3月4日，武汉市红十字会医院，两名刚刚结束工作的医护人员。
March 4, Wuhan City Red Cross Hospital, two just finished work of the medical staff.
中青报 中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄本文约1672字预计阅读时间5分钟作者 | 中青报·中青网记者王嘉兴编辑 | 张国新冠肺炎疫情发展至今，武汉多家医院转为发热患者定点医院已有40余天。
Zhongqing Pneumonia News Correspondent Wang Jiaxing / Photographer About 1672 Words About 5 Minutes Estimated Reading Time By Zhongqing News Zhongqing Zhongqing News Network Reporter Wang Jiaxing has developed an epidemic of pneumonia in Wuhan and many hospitals have been designated for fever sufferers for more than 40 days.
记者最近走访这些医院时，听到多名医护人员建议，要对持续奋战时间长的医护人员优先安排轮休，为“打胜仗”积蓄能量。
During a recent visit to these hospitals, the reporter heard many medical staff advise that medical staff who have been fighting for a long time should be given priority in rotation so as to save energy for "winning battles."
这些人员经过长期高强度工作，身心健康都已严重透支。
After a long period of intense work, these personnel are severely overstretched both physically and mentally.
“我们一直在高负荷、疲劳的状态下持续作战。
"We've been fighting with a lot of stress and fatigue.
”四川省第二批援助湖北医疗队领队黎旭说。
"said Li Xu, the second Sichuan province medical team leader.
1月28日，他和队员抵达武汉，支援武汉市红十字会医院。
On January 28, he and his team arrived in Wuhan to support the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital.
他告诉记者，不管是红十字会医院本院职工，还是陆续抵达的医疗队队员，都很少休息。
He told reporters, whether the Red Cross hospital hospital staff, or the arrival of medical team members, very little rest.
直到最近一周，才有部分人员一周有一到两天休息时间。
Not until the last week did some people get one or two days off a week.
疫情暴发以来，武汉市红十字会医院收治了大量患者，最近一段时间住院病人数仍然处在高位。
Since the outbreak, Wuhan Red Cross hospital admitted a large number of patients, the number of recent hospital patients is still at a high level.
黎旭估算，即使不考虑轮休，医护人员数量都有数百人的缺口。
Even without rotation leave, Li reckons, there are hundreds of gaps in the number of staff.
此外，武汉市红十字会医院收治的病人年龄整体也偏大，不少患者没有生活自理能力，护理任务繁重。
In addition, Wuhan Red Cross hospital treatment of patients overall age is too large, many patients do not have independent living capacity, nursing task is heavy.
疫情暴发以来，医院的护工及后勤人员减少很多，一些医护人员不得不承担护工、保洁等工作，加重了工作负担。
Since the outbreak, hospital nurses and support staff have been reduced considerably, and some health-care workers have had to take on tasks such as nursing and cleaning, adding to the workload.
武汉市红十字会医院的情况不是孤例。
Wuhan Red Cross Hospital is not an isolated case.
记者采访中了解到，定点支援武汉金银潭医院的部分外地医疗队也一直没有轮休。
Reporters in the interview learned that targeted support to Wuhan gold and silver pool hospital some of the medical teams have not been rotation.
武汉市第五医院一名医生告诉记者，医院一直没有安排轮休，甚至一周两天的休息时间也无法保障。
Wuhan Fifth Hospital, a doctor told reporters that the hospital has not been scheduled rotation, or even a two-day weekly rest period can not be guaranteed.
直到上周，一些病休的同事返岗位，才安排部分医护人员休息了2天。
Until last week, some sick colleagues returned to work and some of them were given two days off.
2月10日，国家卫健委、人力资源和社会保障部、财政部出台《关于改善一线医务人员工作条件切实关心医务人员身心健康的若干措施》，提出要根据疫情防控实际，科学测算医务人员工作负荷，合理配置医务人员，既满足医疗服务需求，又保障医务人员休息时间。
On 10 February, the National Health Commission, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security and the Ministry of Finance issued a set of measures to improve the working conditions of front-line medical personnel and ensure their physical and mental health.
国家卫健委副主任曾益新曾表示，前方医护人员工作重，休息条件有限，心理压力大，感染风险高。
Zeng Yixin, deputy director of the National Fitness and Physical Fitness Commission, said that front-line medical staff worked hard, with limited rest conditions, high psychological stress and a high risk of infection.
3月5日，武汉全天新增确诊病例126例，现有确诊病例20115例，疫情比高峰时大有缓解。
On March 5, Wuhan confirmed 126 new cases, the existing confirmed cases of 20115 cases, significantly less than the peak of the disease.
3月6日，中央指导组成员、国务院副秘书长丁向阳介绍，湖北迄今有超过3000名医护人员感染新冠肺炎，其中40%是在医院感染的，60%在社区感染。
More than 3,000 medical workers in Hubei province have contracted pneumonia, 40 percent of them in hospitals and 60 percent in the community, said Ding Xiangyang, a member of the Central Steering Committee and Deputy Secretary-General of the State Council.
2月18日，湖北省人民政府《关于进一步关爱和激励新冠肺炎疫情防控一线医务人员的若干措施》提出：“在方舱医院或一般定点医院工作的一线医护人员，原则上连续工作时间不得长于一个月；在重症救治定点医院的一线医护人员，连续工作时间可适当缩短。
On February 18, the Hubei Provincial People's Government "Measures for Further Care and Motivation of Frontline Medical Personnel for the Prevention and Control of Newly Crowded Pneumonia" proposed that: "In principle, front-line medical personnel working in a cabin hospital or a regular designated hospital should not work for longer than one month.
”武汉市中心医院呼吸内科一名医生告诉记者，自己从1月18日至今没有轮休过。
A doctor at Wuhan Central Hospital told reporters he had not had a rotation since January 18.
科室安排过部分人轮休，但包括他在内，一些医护人员一直没有休息，也不知道什么时候能休息。
Some of the staff were rotated, but some, including him, did not rest and did not know when to rest.
他理解现在的情况，“我们负责的病人没有减少，总不能不管病人。
He understood the situation. "We are not responsible for fewer patients, we can never ignore the patients.
每个科室都上了，科室主任也都顶在一线没有休息。
Each section on the head of the section are also against the line without rest.
”另一位武汉一线医护人员称，他所在的科室一直没有轮休。
Another Wuhan frontline medical worker said there had been no rotation breaks in his department.
他连续工作一个月后，因身体不适向科室主任提出轮休申请，但被告知，申请休息要走请假流程。
After a month of continuous service, he applied to the head of the section for a rotation leave due to ill health, but was informed that the request for rest was subject to a leave process.
本周，他和几名同事终于休息了几天，算是“补休”——补了1月20日以来失去的部分休息时间。
This week, he and several colleagues finally took a few days off, a "catch-up" -- to make up for some of the time lost since January 20.
黎旭认为，要实现医务人员轮休，就需要统筹医疗资源，整合所有医疗队力量。
Lai Xu believes that to achieve rotation of medical staff, we need to pool medical resources and integrate all medical teams.
他告诉记者，就人手紧张、医护人员需要轮休的情况，他于3月1日向国家卫健委提出了支援请求，已有相关部门统筹协调。
He told reporters that because of staff constraints and the need for staff rotation, he had submitted a request for assistance to the National Health Service Commission on March 1.
他理解，现在各地医疗资源紧张。
He understands that medical resources are strained everywhere.
目前，四川累计已向湖北派出10批医疗队、3批疾控队以及国家单独抽调的2名院感专家，共计1459人。
So far, Sichuan has sent 10 medical teams, three batches of disease control teams and two sentinel experts drawn by the state alone to Hubei, totaling 1,459.
国家卫健委医政医管局副局长焦雅辉此前表示，外地援助医疗队轮换休整方案已开始实施，共三种模式，分别为医疗队内部轮换、整建制轮换和重新编组。
The Deputy Director of the Hospital Authority, Jiao Yahui, had said the rotation scheme for medical teams in the field had been implemented, with three modalities: rotation within the medical team, full rotation and regrouping.
据报道，已有福建、山东、云南、河北等地援助湖北的医疗队在工作月余后陆续轮休，甘肃援助湖北医疗队安排医生工作1天休息1.5-2天，护士工作1天休息2.5-3天。
It has been reported that medical teams from Fujian, Shandong, Yunnan and Hebei provinces have been providing assistance to Hubei medical teams on a rotational basis after their working months. Gansu Province has assisted the Hubei Medical Team in arranging for doctors to rest 1.5-2 days a day and nurses to work 2.5-3 days a day.
